text: Alexander Tamanian (, March 4, 1878, Yekaterinodar - February 20, 1936, Yerevan) was an Armenian neoclassical architect, who is remembered today for his work in the city of Yerevan. == Other websites == *Alexander Tamanian at Armeniapedia.org *Alexander Tamanian at TACentral.com Category:Armenian people Category:1878 births Category:1936 deaths Category:20th-century Armenian people
